main event: A round object, size of a dime, was observed moving up and down about 3 times before fading out. No sound was produced.
interesting points: The object was a brilliant light that reduced to a small glow before fading out.
The object was observed for about one minute.
The report states that there was insufficient data to evaluate the sighting.
The location of the sighting was 15 miles south of Dallas, Texas.
The witness was Mrs. Fox, the wife of 'HGUS' from Cedar Hill, Texas.
